comments.body:
Odd, haven't seen that one before. For some reason, on your system, jemalloc thinks it should be cross-compiling. https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=799093 describes a similar situation. Any ideas [~kou]?

As a workaround, does the build succeed with jemalloc off? I see you're building with mimalloc, which should be as good or better than jemalloc anyway.

Side note: I see you're trying to build with ARROW_S3=ON but that's getting turned back OFF because you don't have the necessary system dependencies:

{code}
**** S3 support requires libcurl-devel (rpm) or libcurl4-openssl-dev (deb); building with ARROW_S3=OFF
{code}

The S3 support is another bug.

libcurl-devel is installed on this RHEL8 system but its failing to actually detect that. Maybe a version issue?
{code:java}
rpm -qa | grep libcurl-devel 
libcurl-devel-7.61.1-22.el8.x86_64
 {code}
